  "content": [
    {
      "chapterUid": 3,
      "chapterTitle": "含着微笑的悲歌",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_3_2333-2412",
          "range": "2333-2412",
          "rangeStart": 2333,
          "rangeEnd": 2412,
          "markText": "穷尽现在——不欲其所无，穷尽其所有，重要的不是生活得最好，而是生活得最多，这就是荒谬的人的生活准则。完全没有必要消除荒谬，关键是要活着，是要带着这种破裂去生活",
          "colorStyle": 0,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1703168746,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-21 22:25:46",
          "chapterUid": 3,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2333&rangeEnd=2412",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=2333&rangeEnd=2412"
        },
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_3_1874-1910",
          "range": "1874-1910",
          "rangeStart": 1874,
          "rangeEnd": 1910,
          "markText": "荒谬清楚地说明了欲求统一的精神与令这欲求统一的意念失望的世界之间的分离。",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1702890393,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-18 17:06:33",
          "chapterUid": 3,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1874&rangeEnd=1910",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=3&rangeStart=1874&rangeEnd=1910"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "chapterUid": 6,
      "chapterTitle": "荒谬的墙",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_6_1913-2036",
          "range": "1913-2036",
          "rangeStart": 1913,
          "rangeEnd": 2036,
          "markText": "一旦某一天，“为什么”的问题被提出来，一切就从这带点惊奇味道的厌倦开始了。“开始”是至关重要的。厌倦产生于一种机械麻木生活的活动之后，但它同时开启了意识的运动。它唤醒意识并且激发起随后的活动。随后的活动是无意识地重新套上枷锁，或者是确定性地觉醒。",
          "colorStyle": 0,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1703167612,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-21 22:06:52",
          "chapterUid": 6,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=1913&rangeEnd=2036",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=1913&rangeEnd=2036"
        },
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_6_10780-10807",
          "range": "10780-10807",
          "rangeStart": 10780,
          "rangeEnd": 10807,
          "markText": "荒谬就产生于这种人的呼唤和世界不合理的沉默之间的对抗。",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1703166208,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-21 21:43:28",
          "chapterUid": 6,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=10780&rangeEnd=10807",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=10780&rangeEnd=10807"
        },
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_6_6900-7000",
          "range": "6900-7000",
          "rangeStart": 6900,
          "rangeEnd": 7000,
          "markText": "荒谬在于人，同样也在于世界。它是目前为止人与世界之间的唯一联系。它把人与世界互相联系起来，犹如共同的仇恨能够把诸个存在联系起来一样。这是我能在这个无限的世界中辨别出来的一切，而我就在这个世界遭遇到生活",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1703166205,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-21 21:43:25",
          "chapterUid": 6,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=6&rangeStart=6900&rangeEnd=7000",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=6&rangeStart=6900&rangeEnd=7000"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "chapterUid": 8,
      "chapterTitle": "荒谬的自由",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_8_6208-6318",
          "range": "6208-6318",
          "rangeStart": 6208,
          "rangeEnd": 6318,
          "markText": "如果我确信这种生活只具有荒谬的面貌，如果我感到生活的全部平衡都系于我的意识反抗与这反抗处于其中的黑暗之间永恒的对立，如果我承认我的自由只有与其有限的命运相关联才有意义的话，那我就应该说，重要的并不是活得最好，而是活得最多",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1703166207,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-21 21:43:27",
          "chapterUid": 8,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=8&rangeStart=6208&rangeEnd=6318",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=8&rangeStart=6208&rangeEnd=6318"
        },
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_8_8172-8224",
          "range": "8172-8224",
          "rangeStart": 8172,
          "rangeEnd": 8224,
          "markText": "我的反抗、我的自由和我的激情。仅凭借意识的活动，我就把那邀请我死亡的东西改变成为生活的规则——我拒绝自杀",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1703166203,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-21 21:43:23",
          "chapterUid": 8,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=8&rangeStart=8172&rangeEnd=8224",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=8&rangeStart=8172&rangeEnd=8224"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "chapterUid": 5,
      "chapterTitle": "荒谬的推理",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_5_414-458",
          "range": "414-458",
          "rangeStart": 414,
          "rangeEnd": 458,
          "markText": "真正严肃的哲学问题只有一个：自杀。判断生活是否值得经历，这本身就是在回答哲学的根本问题。",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1703145452,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-21 15:57:32",
          "chapterUid": 5,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=5&rangeStart=414&rangeEnd=458",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=5&rangeStart=414&rangeEnd=458"
        },
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_5_712-786",
          "range": "712-786",
          "rangeStart": 712,
          "rangeEnd": 786,
          "markText": "伽利略曾经坚持过重要的科学真理，然而，当这一真理危及他的生命时，他就轻易地放弃了自己的主张。从某种意义上讲，他做得对。为这个真理遭受火刑是不值得的。",
          "colorStyle": 3,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1702779463,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-17 10:17:43",
          "chapterUid": 5,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=5&rangeStart=712&rangeEnd=786",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=5&rangeStart=712&rangeEnd=786"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "chapterUid": 7,
      "chapterTitle": "哲学性的自杀",
      "items": [
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_7_12280-12302",
          "range": "12280-12302",
          "rangeStart": 12280,
          "rangeEnd": 12302,
          "markText": "荒谬，其实就是指出理性种种局限的清醒的理性。",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1702874855,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-18 12:47:35",
          "chapterUid": 7,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=7&rangeStart=12280&rangeEnd=12302",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=7&rangeStart=12280&rangeEnd=12302"
        },
        {
          "type": "highlight",
          "bookmarkId": "35239384_7_1317-1472",
          "range": "1317-1472",
          "rangeStart": 1317,
          "rangeEnd": 1472,
          "markText": "对这些现象中的任何一种来讲，荒谬感都来自于比较。这样，我就有充分理由说，荒谬感并不来自对一个行为或印象的简单考察，荒谬感是在对一种事实状态和某种现实的比较中、在一个行动和超越这个行动的世界的比较中突然涌现出来。荒谬从根本上讲是一种离异。它不栖身于被比较的诸成分中的任何一个之中，它只产生于被比较成分之间的相遇。",
          "colorStyle": 1,
          "colorLabel": "",
          "createTime": 1702874799,
          "createTimeFormatted": "2023-12-18 12:46:39",
          "chapterUid": 7,
          "appLink": "weread://bestbookmark?bookId=35239384&chapterUid=7&rangeStart=1317&rangeEnd=1472",
          "webLink": "https://weread.qq.com/web/reader/85732ce07219b5d8857ddb1?chapterUid=7&rangeStart=1317&rangeEnd=1472"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
